{
  "design_name": "flare-gated radial stretch",
  "core_claims": [
    "B-only stretching established the radial proper-length actuator and clean peak-dynamics ramp scaling.",
    "The fixed R=sqrt(1+l^2) profile keeps the areal flare active when A_B=0, so R becomes the natural flare-state actuator.",
    "R participation is most useful as flare-curvature gating with a near-fixed core radius during access.",
    "The best tested ordering is B-prestretch -> R-flare-open -> quiet hold -> R-flare-close -> B-reset.",
    "B_setup and B_reset carry essentially zero core negative exposure when R is in the flattened standby profile.",
    "The hold carries the remaining null-contracted exposure, which makes source realism, shoulder compensation, and sampled-stress gates the next work program."
  ],
